b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":1325,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Version Update[Update]","message":"<div><span style=\\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590030000\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>With the addition of The Royal Regimen, we will end Jumpstart Endeavors and certain normal endeavors.<br><br>Rewards for the normal endeavors that will be ended must be accepted by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590559199\\"><\/span>. Please note that if the rewards are not accepted by that time, then you will not be able to receive the rewards, even if you complete the applicable normal endeavors.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><details><summary><span style=\\"color: rgb(44, 130, 201);\\">The list of normal endeavors that will end is as follows.<\/span><\/summary><div>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 10 with a Dragon<br>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 20 with a Dragon<br>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 30 with a Dragon<br>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 30 with Two Dragons<br>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 30 with Three Dragons<br>\\u30fbReach Bond Lv. 30 with Four Dragons<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Halidom to Lv. 3<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Halidom to Lv. 5<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Halidom to Lv. 9<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Halidom to Lv. 10<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Smithy<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Smithy to Lv. 4<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Smithy to Lv. 7<br>\\u30fbUpgrade the Smithy to Lv. 9<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 1 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 2 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 3 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 4 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 5 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 6 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<br>\\u30fbClear Flamehowl Ruins<br>\\u30fbClear Flamehowl Ruins Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear Flamehowl Ruins Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear Waterscour Ruins<br>\\u30fbClear Waterscour Ruins Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear Waterscour Ruins Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear Windmaul Ruins<br>\\u30fbClear Windmaul Ruins Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear Windmaul Ruins Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear Lightsunder Ruins<br>\\u30fbClear Lightsunder Ruins Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear Lightsunder Ruins Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear Shadowsteep Ruins<br>\\u30fbClear Shadowsteep Ruins Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear Shadowsteep Ruins Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear a Dragon Trial<br>\\u30fbClear a Dragon Trial Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear a Dragon Trial Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear a Dragon Trial 10 Times<br>\\u30fbClear The Imperial Onslaught<br>\\u30fbClear The Imperial Onslaught Three Times<br>\\u30fbClear The Imperial Onslaught Five Times<br>\\u30fbClear The Imperial Onslaught 10 Times<br>\\u30fbClear Ch. 10 of the Main Campaign (Normal)<\/div><\/details><\/div><div><br><\/div><hr><div>Version 1.20.0 will be available for download around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590379200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>You may install it when it becomes available; otherwise, an automatic update will occur at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590462000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>When you update to version 1.20.0 and play co-op, you will no longer be matched with players using earlier versions of the game. Rooms created by players playing earlier versions will not display in the Room List, and you will not be able to join them using Find a Room or Join Nearby Players. Additionally, if you input an ID using Enter an ID, the room will display, but you will not be able to enter it. Lastly, rooms created by alliance members playing earlier versions will be visible in the alliance chat, but you will not be able to join the room. The &quot;All set, thanks!&quot; message will display in such cases.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To celebrate the update, we&#39;ll be sending all players a Tenfold Summon Voucher after the automatic update.<\/div><div>This notice will be modified after it has been distributed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: The Tenfold Summon Voucher will not be distributed until after the automatic update, even if you complete the update to version 1.20.0 early.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Update Details<\/div><div>\\u30fbShared skills are here!<\/div><div>You will be able to equip a third and fourth skill, which can only be used by the team&#39;s leader.<\/div><div>Note: Any adventurer in the team can equip shared skills, but only the leader can use them.<\/div><div>You can equip up to two skills that meet the conditions from other adventurers as the first and second shared skill.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/c612f43b4fec47cb4b8858ecc5ce2a89.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25bcShared skills that can be equipped<\/div><div>By meeting all of the conditions for equipping shared skills, you can equip skills from allied adventurers as shared skills.<\/div><div>Note: Some skills cannot be equipped as shared skills, and skills for adventurers who joined during the main campaign can be equipped as shared skills right away.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The conditions for equipping shared skills are as follows.<\/div><div>1. The adventurer whose skills you wish to unlock as shared skills must be at least level 80 and have at least 50 mana nodes unlocked.<\/div><div>2. You must use a specific item on an eligible skill to unlock it as a shared skill.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/6baff93578df7aa3449bbd52345142de.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbThere are some differences between the first and second shared skills in terms of the skills that can be equipped.<\/div><div>First shared skill: If you have a weapon with a weapon skill equipped, you can equip either the weapon skill or a shared skill from an adventurer who has unlocked shared skills.<\/div><div>Second shared skill: If you have a helper selected during solo play, the helper skill will be equipped.<\/div><div>Note: If a weapon skill or helper skill is equipped for the first or second shared skill, you will not be able to use shared skills from other adventurers.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/02dbfb3c08fd445f88967994a813d545.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbYou cannot equip a skill of the same name from the same adventurer you are using.<\/div><div>(Example) Ranzal cannot equip skills from Ranzal, but he can equip skills from Gala Ranzal.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe level of shared skills will match the equivalent skill level for the adventurer who equips it.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25bcSkill point costs for shared skills<\/div><div>Shared skills have a skill point cost.<\/div><div>Skills equipped as the first and second shared skills must fit within the adventurer&#39;s cost limit.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The skill point cost and cost limit vary between skills and adventurers.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/fb68f5eb8e58f9f3bf16370ce46b910e.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25bcRegarding items for unlocking shared skills<\/div><div>Elemental tomes (flame tomes, water tomes, wind tomes, light tomes, and shadow tomes) are required to unlock shared skills. Each one can unlock skills of the corresponding element.<\/div><div>Elemental tomes can be obtained from events and in the shop.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbNew event type: onslaught events<\/div><div>A new event type, the onslaught event, will start in mid-June. Onslaught events will center around solo quests.<\/div><div>Check out the future event notifications for more information.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Royal Regimen is here!<\/div><div>Starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590472800\\"><\/span>, The Royal Regimen will be added to help players who just started playing Dragalia Lost learn how to play the game.<\/div><div>The Royal Regimen has three stages, and clearing all of the endeavors in each stage will allow the player to move to the next stage. By clearing endeavors you will also be able to receive rewards.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/992c41bd91bad83f7e7543b0ab519f1b.png\\"><\/div><div>With the addition of The Royal Regimen, we will also end Jumpstart Endeavors and certain normal endeavors.<\/div><div>Note:&nbsp;<\/div><div>1.Players who cleared the prologue by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590472799\\"><\/span> are eligible for Jumpstart Endeavors.<\/div><div>2.Players who have already started the game will also be able to receive rewards for The Royal Regimen.<\/div><div>3.The following endeavor can be completed by meeting the conditions after <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbView the Wyrmprint Section of the Treasure Trade<\/div><div>4.The following endeavors can be completed either by clearing chapter 5 of the main campaign by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386399\\"><\/span> or by meeting the conditions for the endeavors in version 1.20.0 after <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbUse the Optimize Feature to Form a Flame-Attuned Team<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbUse the Optimize Feature to Form a Water-Attuned Team<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbUse the Optimize Feature to Form a Wind-Attuned Team<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbUse the Optimize Feature to Form a Light-Attuned Team<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbUse the Optimize Feature to Form a Shadow-Attuned Team<\/div><div>5. The following endeavors can be completed either by placing the applicable facilities in the castle grounds by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386399\\"><\/span> or by meeting the conditions for the endeavors after <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Flame Altar on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Dragontree on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Wind Altar on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Water Altar on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Shadow Altar on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Light Altar on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Wind Dracolith on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbPlace a Sword Dojo on the Castle Grounds<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbAdvance the Main Campaign and Place a Water Dracolith<\/div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;\\u30fbAdvance the Main Campaign and Place a Light Dracolith<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdjustments to certain action elements<\/div><div>We will adjust the following action elements to help players better enjoy playing quests.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u3000\\u30fbWe will reduce damage taken by AI adventurers.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Note: When using the auto-play feature, this will apply to allied AI adventurers other than the controlled adventurer.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u3000\\u30fbWe will adjust the combos for certain weapon types. The adjustments are described below.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Sword: We will adjust the attacks so that the adventurer does not jump up with the fourth and fifth attacks.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Blade: We will adjust the power of the fifth attack.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Dagger: We will adjust the attacks so the adventurer does not jump up and move backward with the fifth attack. We will also adjust the power of the fifth attack.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Axe: We will adjust the attacks so that the adventurer does not jump up with the fifth attack.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Wand: We will adjust the speed of the fired shots.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Staff: We will adjust the speed of the fired shots.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u3000\\u30fbAdventurers will no longer take damage from the start of the dodge action to the end of the dodge action.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Note: Adventurers will take damage from some enemy attacks with displayed action markers.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u3000\\u30fbIt will be possible to configure settings in Options under Menu so that adventurers automatically brace themselves.<\/div><div>\\u3000\\u3000Also, adventurers will no longer take damage from when they brace themselves until they are able to move again.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>We plan to make more adjustments to the game&#39;s action elements in the future.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Other Changes<\/div><div>The following adjustments will be applied in a data update to be performed around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will adjust the description text for the adventurer Tiki&#39;s Dragon Scion I and II abilities.<\/div><div>The following changes will be applied in a data update to be performed around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590472800\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will change the name for the Buff Time +X% ability to Buff Skill Time +X%, and will also adjust the description text.<br>\\u3000Note: This change only affects the texts. The effect itself will not change.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Balance Adjustments<\/div><div>The following adjustments will be applied in a data update to be performed around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590386400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will lower the power of the following attacks used by boss enemies in the various Advanced Dragon Trials quests.<\/div><div>High Midgardsormr: Calamitous Storm<\/div><div>High Brunhilda: Scorching Blast<\/div><div>High Mercury: Tidal Explosion<\/div><div>High Jupiter: Supreme Surge<\/div><div>High Zodiark: Cursed Catastrophe<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Issues Fixed<\/div><div>The following issues have been fixed in this version.<\/div><div>\\u30fbUnder certain conditions, the &quot;increases critical rate by 20%&quot; buff granted by the adventurer Ezelith&#39;s Flash of Genius ability sometimes activated more often than intended.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>1. It may take time for the store to reflect the updated information. Players may not be able to perform updates due to their device&#39;s data cache being full. If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device, and then try downloading it from the store.<\/div><div>2. Any adventurers and game screenshots shown are still in development.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590462000\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>As a token of our appreciation, the following item has been sent to players who started playing before <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1590462000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<\/div><div><br>This gift can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after reception. If the gift isn&#39;t retrieved within seven days, it will be lost.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1589781600,"prev_article_id":"1295","next_article_id":"1386","image_path":"","update_time":1590462030}}}'